   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Samuel's Praying for Them without Ceasing,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>so that He Would Not Sin against Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In verse 23a Samuel told the people, who had begged him to pray for them, "As for me, far be it from me that I would sin against Jehovah by ceasing to pray for you."</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>This reveals that Samuel considered not praying for God's peculiar people to be a sin against Jehovah.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>We need to learn of Samuel to pray not only for our own children but also for God's children.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>If we pray for our children without praying for God's children, we may be selfish and sin against God.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Praying for God's children actually includes praying for our children.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>As we pray for God's children, our children will be under His care.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The record in 1 Samuel shows us that Samuel's heart was only for God's elect.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The term elect is precious to the ears of God and to the heart of God.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>His elect are His peculiar, personal possession as a treasure.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Caring for God's elect was a crucial aspect of the history concerning Samuel, which was in sharp contrast to the history concerning Saul.</S>
   </TEXT>
